---
title: Balsamic-Drizzled Skirt Steak with Garlic Herb Toasts and Pear Salad
description: Balsamic vinegar does multiple magical things in this recipe. First, it’s stirred into the sauce to give it an acidity that cuts through and livens up the robust flavor of skirt steak. Then, it’s tossed into an arugula salad and topped with pear, providing a rounded contrast to the sweetness of the fruit. Some of it will inevitably drip into a deep, dark pool on your plate, but luckily the baguette toasts on the side, brushed in a garlic-herb butter, do a swell job of sopping it up.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/balsamic-drizzled-skirt-steak-1f91941a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/balsamic-drizzled-skirt-steak-dd33f322.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-drizzled-skirt-steak-5983800451d3f106a71a2482
nutrition:
  calories: 1050 kcal
  fat: 61 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 75 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 50 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1240 mg
author: HelloFresh
time required: 40m
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve and core @pear{1}; slice into ½-inch wedges. Cut one @demi-baguette{1} into ½-inch cubes. Place pear and baguette cubes on separate sides of a foil-lined #baking sheet{}. Toss each with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp}. Bake until baguette is crispy and pears have softened a bit, about ~{10%minutes}.

Trim, then thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%oz}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook until tender, about ~{7%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Once pear and baguette cubes have baked 10 minutes, remove cubes from sheet and set aside. Flip pear and continue baking until browned, another ~{10%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Season @skirt steak{12%oz} all over with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let rest at least ~{5%minutes} before thinly slicing against the grain.

While steak cooks, halve remaining @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise, then cut in half again crosswise to create quarters. Place half the @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #small bowl{}. Heat in #microwave{} until butter is melted, about ~{30%seconds}. Drizzle mixture over cut sides of baguette. Place on another baking sheet and toast in oven until golden, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Add @water{1/3%cup}, @balsamic vinegar{1%tsp}, @chicken demi-glace{1}, and mushrooms to same pan over medium-high heat and stir, scraping up any brown bits on bottom of pan. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low and let thicken, about ~{1%minute}. Add remaining garlic herb butter and stir until melted.

Toss together @arugula{2%oz}, baguette cubes, remaining @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp}, and @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide steak, salad, and garlic bread between plates. Drizzle sauce over steak. Top salad with pear and crumble over @ricotta salata cheese{1/2%cup}.